== DONOR MILK: THE NEXT BEST THING

If you genuinely cannot breastfeed your baby directly, donor milk from another mother is the next best option — far preferable to formula. Another woman's breast milk still contains living antibodies, immune cells, and the dynamic nutrition that formula simply cannot replicate.

_Formal Milk Banking:_

_#link("https://www.hmbana.org/")[Human Milk Banking Association of North America (HMBANA)]_
- Non-profit network of milk banks across North America
- Donors are screened (health history, blood tests)
- Milk is pasteurized to kill bacteria and viruses while preserving most nutritional benefits
- Primarily reserved for premature and medically fragile infants, but increasingly available for full-term babies
- Requires prescription from pediatrician
- May be covered by insurance for NICU babies
- Cost: \$1-5 per ounce if not covered by insurance

_Informal Milk Sharing:_

_Community-based sharing:_
- Mothers donate milk directly to other mothers
- Common platforms: Human Milk 4 Human Babies (Facebook groups by state), Eats on Feets
- Milk sharing has been practiced throughout human history — wet nursing was the norm for millennia before formula existed
- _Not screened or pasteurized_ — so know your donor
- Risks include disease transmission (HIV, hepatitis, CMV) if the donor's health status is unknown
- Many mothers feel the benefits of human milk outweigh the risks, especially from known and trusted donors

_Flash pasteurization at home:_
- You can pasteurize donor milk at home to reduce risk
- Requires heating milk to 62.5°C (144.5°F) for 30 minutes
- Reduces but doesn't eliminate all pathogens
- Kills some beneficial antibodies in the process, but the milk is still superior to formula

_Why Donor Milk Before Formula:_
Even pasteurized donor milk retains nutritional advantages over formula. It's human milk, made for human babies. Formula is an industrial product designed to approximate what breast milk does — it doesn't come close to matching it. If breastfeeding isn't possible, explore donor milk options before defaulting to formula.

